e slices of 20 ks, 60/70 ks, and 5 ks for\nthe case of the shock acceleration, magnetic reconnection and TEMZ model,\nrespectively. We conclude that, provided that the statistics of the observation\nallows slicing of the data in adequately short time bins, IXPE observations of\nan HSP blazar at a typical flux level can detect the time variability predicted\nby popular models for particle acceleration in jets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Jan 2022 11:12:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Mar 2022 16:07:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-29"}
